# PR Atlas — Core Context

- SPA built with Vite, React, and TypeScript
- Uses pnpm
- Purpose: search technology topics and display related GitHub PRs

## Data

- Topics taxonomy (sections)
- PR-to-topic mappings

## Search

- Token-based + indexed search
- URL-driven state (`?q=`)

---

## Context Strategy (CRITICAL)

- Prefer loading context from docs instead of embedding it
- Never include full documents by default
- Only load specific sections when needed

---

## Documentation Sources

- Architecture → `docs/architecture.md`
- Tailwind conventions → `docs/tailwind-notes.md`
- PR dataset → `pr-inventory.md`

---

## Token Optimization Rules

- Prefer local execution over LLM tasks
- Never process large datasets in a single request
- Use small batches (5–10 items)
- Avoid repeating data
- Store intermediate results
- Use compact representations (IDs over text)

---

## Execution Rules

- If a task can be executed locally, instruct the user to run it
- Do not simulate long-running processes inside the LLM
- Validate commands, then delegate execution
